{"page_content": "![](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/_assets/3137b1a864c689786cac76b3def62dd1/Assets/img/default-banner.jpg)\n\n# Installing and using front-view mirrors\n\nAdding front-view mirrors is a simple, effective and inexpensive way to improve visibility in heavy vehicle blind spots.\n\nHeavy vehicle blind spots can sometimes make it difficult to detect vulnerable road users, particularly at the front and on the forward right side.\n\nA study conducted jointly by the Ministère des Transports, the SAAQ, the city of Montréal and the road safety team at the École Polytechnique de Montréal demonstrated that installing two front-view mirrors is a simple, effective and inexpensive way to improve visibility in these two problematic blind spots.\n\n![Illustration showing the blind spots in front of, on both sides of, and behind a semi-trailer truck.](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/blob/saaq/documents/images/transport_de_biens/antevisuers-zones-angles-morts.jpg)\n\n## Targeted vehicles\n\nFront-view mirrors are primarily intended for heavy vehicles that operate in urban environments. They can be installed on any heavy vehicles with conventional cabs, regardless of the shape or size of the vehicle or the hood.\n\n## Why install front-view mirrors?\n\nFront-view mirrors allow heavy vehicle drivers to see what's in front of their vehicles.", "metadata": {"title": "Installing and using front-view mirrors - SAAQ", "description": "Adding front-view mirrors improves visibility in heavy vehicle blind spots.", "url": "https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/transportation-goods/installing-using-front-view-mirrors", "language": "en", "keywords": "front-view mirrors, heavy vehicles, blind spots, study, visibility", "robots": null, "og_title": "Installing and using front-view mirrors", "og_description": "Adding front-view mirrors improves visibility in heavy vehicle blind spots.", "og_url": "https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/transportation-goods/installing-using-front-view-mirrors", "og_image": "https://saaq.go